CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 17, 1962, pg. 14, reads: "HELP NEEDY - Some of the members of the Chadwick Civic League who recently came to the aid of Mr. and Mrs. Richard Smith and four children, who were burned out of their Westmoreland St. home. Left to right: James Williams, league president; Mrs. Henry S. Thompson, Bernice C. Grayson, secretary of the disaster committee, and Uzel Finney, chairman. Standing: Carl Gunn and Henry H. Caldwell. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Chadwick Civic League, from left: James Williams, Mrs. Henry S. Thompson, Carl Gunn, Bernice C. Grayson, Henry H. Caldwell, and Uzel Finney, posed in interior with jacquard curtains
